he possibility of multiple 'original languages' with no predecessor, but this is purely my intuitive conjecture. Any real analysis would need to pin down (relatively) very accurate estimates both for the genesis of language as well as the beginning of the world migration of the human race. It is my understanding that the incredible difficulty of either task is why the question of some old universal language is usually left alone in favor of more reasonable pursuits, i.e. trying to reconstruct PIE.%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:GradedBy: TA_audrey:)
